<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=missy8595&buddyTimeStamp=20061228&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193060167&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Missy</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>She lives at <a href='/home/?user=missy8595'>27397-A Broadway Boulevard</a> in Metro Park, and can easily walk to <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a> from her home. She's often there, hitting home runs and enjoying the outdoors.<br><br>Since moving to Millsberry on March 30, 2006, Missy has quickly become the go-to girl for info on anything baseball. As the designated hitter on the Millers, Millsberry Academy's baseball team, she has provided Coach Danner's squad with many a clutch hit. She also has a great memory for stats (as all diehard baseball fans do) and can recall minute details from past seasons. So if you ever have any questions about baseball, Missy is a great resource.<br><br>When she's not thinking in terms of balls and strikes, she's listening to music. She's got turntables and a jukebox in her home for listening to her favorite pop and country tunes. Sometimes she'll find herself humming new melodies, and wants to one day set them down on paper with lyrics.<br><br>This winter, Missy is enjoying the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Clothing Store</a>'s holiday offerings, and spent the past week exchanging gifts with her best buddies thanks to the new package delivery system. As for her hopes for 2007, she's looking forward to baseball season in the spring, and can't wait to see what new excitement Millsberry has in store for her. <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Missy, and congrats on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
